@12881    = ~Tome of the Dedicated Specialist~
@12882    = ~The text in this tome shifts and changes depending on which person is reading it, though only a wizard will see any text at all. For any specialist wizard, this text contains great magical knowledge, but it comes with an unbreakable curse: the wizard must forever rely on the spells they learned in the book, foregoing all others.

STATISTICS:

Special:
  A specialist wizard who reads this book learns every wizard spell of their school, but cannot cast wizard spells of any other school.
Weight: 8 lb.~
@12883    = ~Silvered Masterwork Spear~
@12884    = ~One of man's earliest weapons, dating back to the most primitive of times, the first spears were simply wooden poles or sticks sharpened at one end. When man mastered metals, spearheads were made from iron and steel. Having reached this end, weaponers began experimenting with different types of spear heads, thus leading to the development of certain polearm types. This particular spear has a head of silver, making it effective against lycanthropes and devils.

STATISTICS:

Damage:  1d8
Attack Bonus: +1 
Damage Type:  Piercing
Special:
  Counts as a silver weapon
Weight: 6 lb.
Feat Requirement:  Martial Weapon, Polearm
Type:  Two-handed~
@12885    = ~Rogue's Cowl~
@12886    = ~This dark brown cowl is meant to be worn on the head and over the shoulders as a broad hood. It was crafted by the gnomish rogue and illusionist Brein Chestnut. Brein used the cowl on his own adventures for several years before his childhood sweetheart convinced him to settle down. He gave the cowl to his nephew, Chirchet, who in turn sold the item for a large stretch of farmland.

STATISTICS:

Generic Armor Bonus: +2
Hide in Shadows: +4
Move Silently: +4
Weight: 2 lb.~
